    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Leather-finishing tools, often used by shoemakers, that consist of one or more small wheels with a crimped edge mounted on a handle; the wheels are rolled over the leather to create a broken line.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
